title: ICE during rustc rebuild due to modifying the rustc test suite

labels.name: I-ICE
labels.description: Issue: The compiler panicked, giving an Internal Compilation Error (ICE) ❄️

labels.name: T-compiler
labels.description: Relevant to the compiler team, which will review and decide on the PR/issue.

labels.name: A-spurious
labels.description: Area: Spurious failures in builds (spuriously == for no apparent reason)

labels.name: E-needs-mcve
labels.description: Call for participation: This issue needs a Minimal Complete and Verifiable Example

body:
### Code `src/test/ui/fn/issue-80844-no-gate.rs` ```diff fn returns_generator() -> _ { //~^ ERROR the type placeholder `_` is not allowed within types on item signatures [E0121] //~| NOTE not allowed in type signatures || yield 0 //~^ ERROR yield syntax is experimental - //~^ NOTE see issue + //~^ NOTE no } ``` ```console $ CARGO_LOG=cargo::core::compiler::fingerprint=info ./x.py test src/test/ui/fn |& tee test.log ``` This did not happen every time I tried to change the test. ### Meta Using `rustc` built from [PatchMixolydic/rust/issue-80844](https://github.com/PatchMixolydic/rust/tree/issue-80844), which only has [this change](https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/pull/80847) applied. ### Error output I was not able to reproduce the ICE to get a backtrace without having to rebuild `rustc`.
